{"name": "pybigtools", "metadata": {"name": "pybigtools", "version": "0.2.3", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Rust", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Bio-Informatics"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy"], "summary": "Python bindings to the Bigtools Rust library for high-performance BigWig and BigBed I/O", "upload_time": 1732745538}, "documentation": ["The `pybigtools` python package wraps the `bigtools` Rust library and allows effecient reading and writing of bigWig and bigBed files.\n\n## Documenation\n\nDocumentation is available on [readthedocs](https://bigtools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/pybigtools.html).\n\n## Examples\n\n(Replace `<path>` with the path to a bigWig file or url)\n\n### Iterator of intervals\n\n```python\nimport pybigtools\nb = pybigtools.open(<path>)\ni = b.intervals(\"chr1\")\nprint(next(i))\n```\n\n### Numpy array of values\n\n```python\nimport pybigtools\nb = pybigtools.open(<path>)\na = b.values(\"chr1\")\nprint(a.shape)\n```\n\n### Open a file-like object\n\n```python\nimport pybigtools\nb = pybigtools.open(open(<path>, 'rb'))\na = b.values(\"chr1\")\nprint(a.shape)\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pybigtools.pybigtools", "documentation": ["ruff: noqa: F403", "ruff: noqa: F405", "This is here to make sure that source installs with pip work correctly"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pybigtools.pybigtools.__doc__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pybigtools.pybigtools.bt", "xref": {"fqname": "pybigtools.pybigtools", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pybigtools.tests.examples", "documentation": ["While the built-in `bigWigAverageOverBed` uses compiled code for speed,", "you could also implement as so"], "functions": [{"name": "pybigtools.tests.examples.bigWigAverageOverBed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "bigWig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bed", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "names", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Gets the average values from a bigWig over the entries of a bed file.\n\nParameters:\n    bigWig (str): The path to the bigWig.\n    bed (str): The path to the bed.\n    names (None, bool, or int):\n        If `None`, then each return value will be a single `float`,\n            the average value over an interval in the bed file.\n        If `True`, then each return value will be a tuple of the value of column 4\n            and the average value over the interval with that name in the bed file.\n        If `False`, then each return value will be a tuple of the interval in the format\n            `{chrom}:{start}-{end}` and the average value over that interval.\n        If `0`, then each return value will match as if `False` was passed.\n        If a `1+`, then each return value will be a tuple of the value of column of this\n            parameter (1-based) and the average value over the interval.\n\nReturns:\n    This returns a generator of values. (Therefore, to save to a list, do `list(bigWigAverageOverBed(...))`)\n    If no name is specified (see the `names` parameter above), then returns a generator of `float`s.\n    If a name column is specified (see above), then returns a generator of tuples `({name}, {average})`"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pybigtools.tests.test_bigwig", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pybigtools.tests.test_bigwig.retrieve_encode_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "accession", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filetype", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybigtools.tests.test_bigwig.test_bigwig_read", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pybigtools.tests.test_bigwig.test_b